OL,3,CFire chief claims responding to fire
OL,4,Calarms is 'waste of resources'
OL,6,F"We'd rather use that time more
OL,7,Feffectively, driving down the risk in
OL,8,Fthe community rather than driving down
OL,9,Fthe road on blue lights, putting
OL,10,Fpeople at risk."
OL,12,FESFRS attends an average of 10,000
OL,13,Fincidents each year. Automatic fire
OL,14,Falarm systems account for 36% of
OL,15,Fcalls, of which 97% turn out to be
OL,16,Ffalse alarms.
