OL,3,CFire chief claims responding to fire
OL,4,Calarms is 'waste of resources'
OL,6,FThe service says this causes
OL,7,F"significant disruption to our
OL,8,Ftraining, fire safety and community
OL,9,Fsafety work and, crucially, while
OL,10,Ffirefighters are investigating the
OL,11,Fcause of the alarm, they cannot attend
OL,12,Femergencies where lives are at risk".
OL,14,FWest Sussex Fire and Rescue Service
OL,15,Fmade a similar change of policy in
OL,16,F2022. Since then, the brigade said it
OL,17,Fhad responded to 183 fewer false
OL,18,Falarms.
